 The National Universities Commission has unbundled Mass Communication degree in Nigerian universities. The degree has now been split into seven with students having to pick a major area of interest. According to NUCâ€™s Executive Secretary, Prof Abubakar Rasheed, who disclosed the information on Thursday, the decision will take effect from 2020 admissions and academic sessions. The seven new programmes/departments to be domiciled in a faculty/school/college of communication and media studies are Journalism and Media Studies, Public Relations, Advertising, Broadcasting, Film and Multi-Media Studies, Development Communication Studies, Information and Media Studies.